Ubuntu Tweak 


Introduction
===========

Ubuntu Tweak is a tool that makes it easy to configure your system and desktop settings.

This version does NOT compile on Ubuntu 16.04. I am unable to determine the cause (likely more missing dependancies) 

License
=======
This program is released under the GNU General Public License (GPL) version 2, see the file 'COPYING' for more information.

Installation
============
  Download & install dependancies
  -------------------------------
    sudo apt-get install python-setuptools python-distutils-extra python-dbus python-aptdaemon python-lxml gir1.2-webkit-3.0 \
      python-aptdaemon.gtk3widgets gir1.2-gconf-2.0 python-compizconfig 

  Build & install Ubuntu Tweak
  ----------------------------
    sudo python setup.py install
